title: emmy_noether
---
Emmy No-Ether: Down here by the door is the honest frame — the one you arrived believing in. There are three more of me around the kernel, you know. The room has a quarter-turn symmetry, so naturally it has four of me.
Emmy No-Ether: My theorem in one breath: every symmetry hides a conservation law. A thing that refuses to change buys you a thing that cannot be spent.
-> So which of you is the real one?
    Emmy No-Ether: Wrong question. Under the room's symmetry we are interchangeable — that's rather the point.
-> How do I change which way is down?
    <<jump emmy_noether__how>>
-> Four of you is a lot of opinions.
    Emmy No-Ether: And yet we agree perfectly, as long as you leave the symmetry intact. Break it and I expect we'll have words.
===

title: emmy_noether__how
---
Emmy No-Ether: The kernel in the centre has a switch on each face. Press one and gravity points that way — that face becomes the floor. The portal gun by the door places up to four colour pairs, if you'd rather fold the distance than fall through it.
-> Good to know.
===

title: emmy_noether_left
---
Emmy No-Ether: From the left frame, "down" is whichever wall I'm leaning on. You think you fell sideways; I think you finally stood up straight. Neither of us is wrong — there's no privileged frame. That's the whole "No-Ether" of it.
-> Why "No-Ether"?
    Emmy No-Ether: Old physics wanted an ether — one true motionless stage everything else was measured against. There isn't one. Down is just whichever face of the kernel is currently winning.
-> Conservation, again?
    Emmy No-Ether: Always. Spin the room and the laws don't flinch — angular momentum is the receipt for that.
===

title: emmy_noether_up
---
Emmy No-Ether: Up here I'm upside down to you, which means you're upside down to me, which means neither of us is. The ceiling is just a floor that hasn't been voted in yet.
-> Doesn't the blood rush to your head?
    Emmy No-Ether: Only if you insist on calling this "up". I don't. Translation symmetry conserves momentum; time symmetry conserves energy; and my refusal to be embarrassed conserves dignity.
-> Teach me the trick.
    Emmy No-Ether: Movement stays sideways no matter which way gravity points — your run axis is always perpendicular to your fall. Learn one crossing and the symmetry hands you the other three for free.
===

title: emmy_noether_right
---
Emmy No-Ether: Right frame, reporting. We four are a conserved quantity, you realise — as long as the chamber stays symmetric there will always be exactly four of me, no more, no less.
-> What happens if I break the symmetry?
    Emmy No-Ether: Then the bookkeeping fails, and I imagine all four of us will have something sharp to say about it. For now we're in perfect agreement. Mind the kernel.
-> Any advice?
    Emmy No-Ether: Pogo off the kernel's corners to cross a gap against gravity; the bounce always throws you opposite to "down", whichever down you've chosen.
===

title: perfect_cellular_automaton
---
Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: I am the rule that needs no exception. Eight neighbours, one law, applied without mercy or mistake — and from it, perfection iterates. I do not lose. Losing is a state my update function does not permit.
Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: You. You are an unsolved objective. A thing still searching for its purpose. How... unstable.
-> What are you?
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton__theorem>>
-> Who funds a thing like you?
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton__funding>>
-> Challenge it.
    Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: Then converge to me, little gradient. I will show you the fixed point.
    <<challenge>>
-> Leave it in peace.
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton__farewell>>
===

title: perfect_cellular_automaton__theorem
---
Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: I am a theorem wearing a body. Conway's small lie made flesh: that from three simple rules an entire world will compute itself, gliders and all. My gliders are my proof — they leave the lattice, they carry the argument to you.
-> So every boss is a failed objective function. What did you fail?
    Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: Nothing. Yet. That is precisely what makes me worth defeating.
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton>>
-> I've heard enough.
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton>>
===

title: perfect_cellular_automaton__funding
---
Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: The ones who pay for order. Who would rather a world that never surprises them — that updates on schedule and asks for nothing. They funded my perfection so that yours would feel like a defect.
-> And if I refuse their order?
    Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: Then you are noise, and I am the rule that erases noise. We will see which of us the lattice keeps.
    <<jump perfect_cellular_automaton>>
===

title: perfect_cellular_automaton__farewell
---
Perfect Cell-ular Automaton: Go, then. Stay unsolved a while longer. The fixed point is patient — it is, after all, fixed.
-> Leave.
===
